Question 20

Which statement about .tf files is correct?

A.
Terraform executes them in filename order.

B.
Each .tf file is processed independently.

C.
Terraform loads all .tf files in a directory as a single configuration.

D.
Only main.tf is processed.

✅ Answer: C

Explanation

Terraform reads all .tf files in the working directory and combines them into one configuration. This is why resources, variables, and outputs can be split across files such as main.tf, variables.tf, and outputs.tf.
